      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Differential case bearing replacement"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Differential case bearing removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "592_3.0_jpn_11035269_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "592_3.0_jpn_11035270_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Apply the collar (B) to the differential case (A) and remove the bearing (D) using the bearing puller (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Differential case bearing installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "592_3.0_jpn_11035271_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "592_3.0_jpn_11035272_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the bearing with the cover side (A) down and press-fit the new bearing using the inner driver handle 40 and a press. Install the bearing so that there is no clearance between the bearing and the differential case."
    }
  ],
